'''Secrets''' in Chrono Trigger include hidden items, optional content, and special features.

== Secret Characters ==

=== Magus ===
An optional party member who can be recruited late in the game.

'''How to Recruit:'''
* After the Ocean Palace events, face Magus at North Cape
* Choose to spare him instead of fighting
* He joins the party as a permanent member

'''Notes:'''
* Magus cannot use combination Techs with other characters
* His magic is Shadow-elemental
* Recruiting him means missing the battle rewards from fighting him

== Hidden Items ==

=== Rainbow Shell ===
A special item required for the best equipment.

'''Location:'''
* Found in the Giant's Claw in 600 AD
* Accessed after the Tyranno Lair events
* Required for Rainbow and Prism equipment

=== Sun Stone ===
Powers the ultimate weapon equipment.

'''Process:'''
# Obtain the Moon Stone from the Sun Palace in 2300 AD
# Place it in the Sun Keep in 65,000,000 BC
# Retrieve it in 2300 AD after charging through time
# Note: Must prevent theft in 1000 AD by checking on it

== Secret Locations ==

=== Ozzie's Fort ===
An optional dungeon with comedic boss fights.

'''Access:'''
* Available after Magus's Castle
* Located in 600 AD
* Features rematch battles with Ozzie, Flea, and Slash

=== Sunken Desert ===
Hidden dungeon accessible in 600 AD.

'''Requirements:'''
* Must have completed certain story events
* Contains the Retinite boss
* Rewards include Fiona's sidequest

== New Game Plus ==

After completing the game, New Game Plus offers:

'''Features:'''
* Keep all levels, equipment, and techs
* Access to additional ending variations
* Fight Lavos at different points for different endings

'''Multiple Endings:'''
There are 13+ different endings depending on when and how you defeat Lavos:
* "Beyond Time" - Standard ending
* "Reunion" - Special character ending
* "The Dream Project" - Developer room ending (defeat Lavos immediately in New Game+)
* And many more...

